'''Abecedarian''', ''[[noun (part of speech)|noun]]'' [L. ''abecedarius''. A word from the first four letters of the alphabet.]

<ol>
<li>One who is learning the alphabet; hence, a tyro.

<li> One engaged in [[teaching]] the alphabet. ''[[Wood (source)|Wood]].''
</ol>
-----
{ '''Abecedarian''', '''Abecedary''', } ''[[adjective (part of speech)|adjective]]''

Pertaining to, or formed by, the letters of the alphabet; [[alphabetic]]; hence, [[rudimentary]].

'''Abecedarian psalms''', '''hymns''', etc., compositions in which (like the 119th [[psalm]] in Hebrew) distinct portions or verses [[commence]] with successive letters of the alphabet. ''[[Hook (source)|Hook]].''